        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(macos): document Darwin kernel version fallback for macOS 26+",
        "body": "Fixes #95145\n\n## Summary\n\nOpenClaw host detection could report the wrong macOS version when `sw_vers` is unavailable (CI, containers). The fallback `os.release()` returns the Darwin kernel version (e.g. 25.5.0 on macOS 26 Tahoe), which no longer maps to macOS marketing version via the old Darwin-minus-4 formula.\n\nThe code already uses `sw_vers -productVersion` as the primary source. This change documents the Darwin kernel mapping shift in the fallback path so future maintainers don't apply the outdated formula.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- [x] This change is backwards compatible\n- [x] This change has been tested\n- [ ] I have updated relevant documentation (N/A)\n- [ ] Breaking changes (if any) are documented in Summary (N/A)\n\nCloses: #95145",
        "branch": "fix/issue-95145-macos-version",
